{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a289996d-f402-4d86-b58d-5784f0d1cebb","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n**In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Remove** the separate `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package reference\n3. **Add** the single `MSTest` v3 meta-package (it bundles the test framework, adapter, *and* test SDK)\n\n**In `OrderServiceTests.cs`:** No changes needed — MSTest v3 uses the same namespace and attributes (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`, etc.).\n\nWant me to apply these changes to your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cee0ffb9-66f4-459e-b289-24694072d275","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has:\n1. A `.csproj` targeting `net462` with an assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. A test file using `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3, they need to:\n\n1. **Remove** the assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` NuGet package (v3.x) — MSTest v3 ships as a single meta-package called `MSTest`\n\n\n3. **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version, though MSTest v3's meta-package may handle this dependency. Also need to verify the target framework — MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+, so `net462` should work, though upgrading to a newer framework is generally recommended.\n\nActually, the `MSTest` meta-package bundles everything together including the test SDK, so I can remove the separate reference. The key changes are swapping out the old assembly reference for the `MSTest` v3 NuGet package, and the using statements in the code stay the same since they're already pointing to the right namespace.","outputTokens":734,"requestId":"BD02:158C5C:204DE80:249F043:6A07D8CC"},"id":"260e1600-e011-4bbf-b174-8dede282dc29","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:39:22.760Z"